# Circuit Diagram: Jet Nozzle Flow System - Arduino Sensor Interface
# This is a text placeholder for the circuit diagram
# The actual schematic should be created in:
# - Fritzing (open-source, visual)
# - KiCAD (professional PCB design)
# - LTspice (circuit simulation)

# Signal Flow:
# Pressure Sensor → Analog Signal → Arduino A0
# Temperature Sensor → Analog Signal → Arduino A1
# Flow Rate Sensor → Digital Pulse (5kHz max) → Arduino D2 (INT0)
# Velocity Sensor → Digital Pulse (5kHz max) → Arduino D3 (INT1)
# Power: 5V from Arduino to all sensors
# Ground: Common ground for all components

# Connection Details:
# Sensor VCC → Arduino 5V
# Sensor GND → Arduino GND
# Sensor OUT → Corresponding Arduino Pin (A0, A1, D2, D3)

# Add 0.1µF bypass capacitors near sensor inputs
# Add 10kΩ pull-up resistors on digital inputs (D2, D3)

[See hardware_setup.md for detailed wiring instructions]
